Charter International, GDF Suez, Sanofi: European Equity Preview

-- B y   I n y o u n g   H w a n g
-- 
2011-09-14T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/charter-international-gdf-suez-sanofi-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
be active in European trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  The Stoxx  Europe  600 Index rose 0.9 percent to 220.87. The
Stoxx 50 Index climbed 1.3 percent to 2,082.51. The Euro Stoxx
50 Index, a benchmark for nations using the euro, advanced 2.1
percent to 2,036.64.  Charter International Plc (CHTR)  : The welding and
automation-equipment maker has “engaged with Melrose but the
ball is now in Melrose’s court,” DealReporter said, citing a
source close to Charter. Fulton, Maryland-based Colfax Corp.
agreed to buy Charter for 1.53 billion pounds ($2.41 billion),
trumping Melrose’s bid. The stock dropped 0.2 percent to 855
pence.  GDF Suez (GSZ)  SA: Europe’s largest gas network operator
said results from exploratory drilling in the  Caspian Sea  under
the Absheron license were “extremely promising.” Shares rose
0.2 percent to 19.66 euros.  Sanofi SA (SAN FP): Riccardo Perfetti, vice president of
medical affairs at the drugmaker’s diabetes division, said its
Lyxumia diabetes drug has shown no cause for concern about
possible links to cancer. The shares rose 0.4 percent to 46.69
euros.  Vinci SA (DG)  : The construction company said it won a
sewer system contract valued at 108 million euros in the
 Dominican Republic . The shares gained 0.8 percent to 31.67
euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
